  "from": "mcp.test.dki2@gmail.com",
  "date": "Sun, 11 May 2025 07:09:52 -0700",
  "snippet": "Hi MedTech Solutions Team, I hope you&#39;re doing well. As we prepare for the scheduled software update to our scheduling and management platform on April 15th, we want to make sure everything goes",
  "body": "Hi MedTech Solutions Team,\n\nI hope you’re doing well. As we prepare for the scheduled software update to our scheduling and management platform on April 15th, we want to make sure everything goes smoothly on both sides. Below is a summary of our key requirements and a few questions we’d like to clarify:\n\n1. Planned Downtime\n   • Please confirm the exact maintenance window (start/end times and time-zone).\n   • We need at least two weeks advance notice if the window changes so we can inform staff and patients.\n\n2. Data Integrity & Backups\n   • We require a full, point-in-time backup of our environment before the update begins.\n   • Kindly outline the verification steps you’ll take post-update to ensure no data loss or corruption.\n\n3. New Feature Roll-Out\n   • The April release is expected to introduce enhanced appointment-scheduling workflows.\n   • Could you provide user documentation or release notes no later than April 8th so we can update our internal knowledge base?\n\n4. Staff Training & Support\n   • We would like a 1-hour virtual walk-through of the new features for our front-desk and clinical teams during the week of April 11th.  \n   • Please confirm what support channels will be available during the first 48 hours after go-live.\n\n5. Security & Compliance\n   • Our environment must remain HIPAA- and HITRUST-compliant.  \n   • Please share a brief summary of the security enhancements included in this release and any recent penetration-test results that are safe to disclose.\n\n6. Rollback & Contingency Plan\n   • In the unlikely event of an issue, what is the estimated recovery time to revert to the previous stable version?\n\n7. Staging/Preview Environment\n   • If possible, we’d like access to a staging environment with the release candidate by April 4th to perform basic workflow testing with sample data.\n\nIf any of the above requirements pose a challenge, let us know as soon as possible so we can adjust plans accordingly.\n\nThank you for your partnership, and please confirm receipt of this message at your earliest convenience.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n[Your Organization]\n[Phone]\n"
}","annotations":null}

